{{wikipedia}}
==English==
===Noun===
'''polar coordinates''' ''plural''

# {{mathematics}} The [[coordinate]]s of a point in a plane, measured as its [[Cartesian distance]] from the [[origin]] and the angle measured [[anticlockwise]]/[[counterclockwise]] from the [[x-axis|''x''-axis]] to a line joining the point to the origin.
# {{mathematics}} The coordinates of a point in three-dimensional space, measured as its Cartesian distance from the origin, the angle measured from the z-axis to a line joining the point to the origin, and the angle measured anticlockwise from the x-axis to this line.

